                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>The beginning of this inscription is lost, but from palaeography and the letters <hi rend="italic">Nan</hi> traceable in the first line, it may be assigned to <hi rend="bold">Nandivarman III.</hi> It is dated in the <hi rend="bold">18th year</hi> and registers the gift of 96 sheep by the shepherds <hi rend="italic">(kōṭṭamaṉṟāḍis)</hi> of Āmūr-kōṭṭam for burning a perpetual lamp before the god Perumā[ṉa*]ḍigaḷ ‘who was pleased’ to stand at Viḻupperundāya-Vishṇugṛiham in Paḍuvūr.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
